@page "/createcharacter/aquamarine"
@using Components.Buttons
<h1>The Aquamarine Arcanist</h1>

<h3>Kin: The people of Lorien</h3>
<h3>Mission: There is someone who stalks the dreams of humans. Find them and stop them before they trap whole nations in the living death.</h3>
<p>Lorien is the master of dreams, visions and sleep. His people have a mystical quality, and among their numbers is a certain gray wizard.</p>
<p>The color aquamarine is a natural color that looks artificial, much as the world of dreams feels real when it is in fact a vision. Or is it?</p>
<p>You are a dreamweaver, a master of psychic powers and telekinesis.</p>
<p>Inherent strengths:
    <ul>
        <li>You learn telekinetic and psychic powers very quickly. +10% to psychic magic learning.</li>
        <li>You can enter the land of dreams and trap people there, effectively killing them while trapping them in their dreams. +3 Willpower in the land of dreams only.</li>
        <li>You can use both telekinesis and telepathy. +1 agility when using telekinesis.</li>
        <li>You recharge your magic by cleansing the thoughts of a corrupted creature.</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<p>
    Inherent weaknesses:
    <ul>
        <li>You are weak to overly skeptical people, especially humans. -1 Willpower when interacting with humans.</li>
        <li>Although you walk the land of dreams, other animals can trap you there to. It isn't permanent, but Lorien is getting tired of releasing you.</li>
        <li>You are a bit squishy outside of the land of dreams. -1 Strength when outside the land of dreams</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<h4>Starting Stats</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>+4 Willpower (WP): Represents mental fortitude and resistance to magical corruption.</li>
        <li>+6 Wisdom (WD): Indicates knowledge of lore, understanding of nature, and strategic thinking.</li>
        <li>+0 Agility (AG): Determines speed, reflexes, and ability to navigate terrain.</li>
        <li>+0 Strength (ST): Reflects physical power and endurance.</li>
    </ul>
<div>
    <MyButton ButtonText="Back To Color Choices" OnClick="ReturnToColorChoices" />
    <MyButton ButtonText="Choose Aquamarine" OnClick="ChooseAquamarine" />
</div>
<div>
    <img src="images/lorien.jpg" alt="Lorien" />
</div>
@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager
@code {
    private void ReturnToColorChoices()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
    private void ChooseAquamarine()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
}